children.subject: Still looking for an answer to this ^^ pls help

With the current system, in order to get into the class, you'll necessarily have to be waitlisted for an open section. This means that you are likely going to end up being stuck on the waitlist at some point unless you change things.

I think the best thing to do right now is to drop and re-enroll yourself for the discussion/lab that have the maximum number of open seats. Your discussion/lab waitlist position determines your waitlist position in the class, not the lecture. So even if your lecture waitlist position is going to increase by a fair bit, your lab/discussion waitlist position would be lesser and you'd have a much higher chance of getting in, as compared to nil currently.
I mean, if you're first on the waitlist for your current lab/discussion, then it doesn't make sense to switch. If you're near the end, then switching seems reasonable.
Ok, thanks so much! Where can I find what position I am on the waitlist? I've looked but can't find it anywhere.
And by position on the waitlist I mean waitlist position of the lab AND waitlist position of the discussion

You can't see this information anywhere. You may be able to kind of guess, based on knowing how many people were on the waitlist when you waitlisted. You can also get a loose estimate based on your position in the class waitlist.

OP here,

Should I drop the class and enroll in a different lab/ discussion? I'm scared that this will put me even further down the waitlist.

history.content:
You do not qualify for any seats in the lecture (see http://classes.berkeley.edu/content/2018-spring-eleng-16a-001-lec-001), and both the lab and the discussion you selected are full.

So, there's 3 reasons you can't get into the course right now.
